a for the decade ahead. In nine previously unpublished essays, they address current policies in education, health insurance, welfare, low-income housing, health care and pensions for older Americans, and aid to the poor of other nations. Concluding chapters show how limited resources can finance more effective social policies, and assess the political prospects for policy reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aAaron, Henry J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBane, Mary Jo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruton, Henry J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuban, Larry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGramlich, Edward M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKain, John F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcPherson, Michael S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPechman, Joseph A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeterson, Paul E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinhardt, Uwe E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150173887640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501738876423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501738876/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles